id: pm-2nqx
title: Test-suite dedup & best-practice audit (post module-mirror reorg)
description: "READ-ONLY audit of tests/unit (216 spec files, 4236 tests, 100/100/100/100 coverage) after the module-mirror reorg. Parent epic: pm-xau3. Goal was finding (1) cross-file duplicate test cases and (2) best-practice deviations. NO EDITS made here; lead agent must re-verify 100% coverage holds after any merge (a dedup must not drop a uniquely-covered branch).\n\n== CONFIRMED DUPLICATE CLUSTERS (ranked by impact) ==\n\n[D1 HIGH] background-refresh module tested twice. tests/unit/core/search/background-refresh.spec.ts (dedicated module spec) vs tests/unit/core/search/search-cache.spec.ts lines ~1712-1946. Both import the SAME src/core/search/background-refresh.js. search-cache re-tests shouldRunSearchRefreshInForeground, queue enqueue/drain, and runSemanticRefreshWorker that background-refresh.spec.ts already owns. Safe merge: delete the duplicated describe blocks from search-cache.spec.ts (lines ~1712-1946) AFTER porting the few search-cache-UNIQUE cases into background-refresh.spec.ts. See comment for exact unique-case lists. ~200 line reduction.\n\n[D2 MEDIUM] check-secrets line-numbering + include/exclude rules tested twice. tests/unit/scripts/check-secrets-rules.spec.ts vs tests/unit/scripts/check-secrets-lib.spec.ts. Both exercise scanContent line numbers + includeFiles/excludeFiles. See comment for the overlap/unique split.\n\nNo other CONFIRMED cross-file duplicates. Commands/cli, extensions/mcp/sdk/scripts agents found only LEGITIMATE separation (parser-vs-e2e, unit-vs-integration, per-command tracker-not-initialized smoke tests). The shared \"fails when tracker is not initialized\" test name across ~27 command specs is correct (each tests a different command), NOT a duplicate.\n\n== BEST-PRACTICE FINDINGS (ranked) ==\n\n1. [MED] Brittle real setTimeout/sleep instead of vi.useFakeTimers(): extension-loader.spec.ts lines ~5030/5043/5067 (deactivate-timeout tests, 25-35ms real waits, CI-flaky); telemetry-runtime.spec.ts lines ~51/1224/1678; item-store.spec.ts ~469/489; embedding-batches.spec.ts ~243. Short waits so low-flake-risk but non-deterministic.\n2. [MED] Monolithic covers-everything tests in telemetry-runtime.spec.ts (e.g. lines ~1423, ~1765) with 50+ assertions each; hard to localize a failure. Consider splitting by branch area (no coverage change).\n3. [LOW] Verbose inline env save/restore in telemetry-runtime.spec.ts afterEach (~lines 63-107). A withCleanEnv() helper already exists in background-refresh.spec.ts (~86-111); adopt it.\n4. [LOW] extension-loader.spec.ts (5656 lines, 106 tests) under-nested: many describe blocks hold 20+ flat tests; add nested describes for readability.\n5. [LOW] Real git spawnSync helper in extension-command.spec.ts (~line 81) depends on system git; consider mocking unless integration is intentional.\n\n== POSITIVES ==\nGood isolation overall: temp-dir scoping via withTempDir/withTempPmPath, mocked fetch (no real network), spies for console, try/finally restore of globals, no module-level orphan it()."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: audit,tech-debt,testing
