  "2026-06-16T07:09:24.880Z",claude-code-agent,"[D1 HIGH] background-refresh duplicate — exact safe-merge map. Both files import src/core/search/background-refresh.js.\n\nDUPLICATED (identical code path + assertions), present in BOTH:\n- shouldRunSearchRefreshInForeground: bg-refresh 114/119/131/138/153 vs search-cache 1717/1722/1753 (inline-under-vitest default; explicit inline override; worker-child marker).\n- queue enqueue/drain: bg-refresh \"merges/dedupes/sorts then drains\" 162, \"ignores empty/blank\" 171, \"malformed json / non-array\" 179, \"removes stale gate\" 195 vs search-cache 1760/1773/1781/1790/1809.\n- runSemanticRefreshWorker: bg-refresh \"drains+refreshes under lock\" 300, \"settings cannot be read warning\" 286, \"re-enqueues+warns on throw\" 341, \"returns without draining when lock held\" 352, \"returns early when pm root missing\" 276 vs search-cache 1848/1908/1927/1891/1939.\n\nUNIQUE to search-cache.spec.ts (MUST be ported into background-refresh.spec.ts before deletion, or coverage drops):\n- \"falls back to an unguarded queue merge when the pending queue gate stays contended\" (1797)\n- \"keeps awaited queue-gate backoff timers referenced so CLI top-level await can settle\" (1822)\n- \"processes ids enqueued mid-refresh in a follow-up round\" (1864)\nNOTE: bg-refresh has near-equivalents (1797~bg 207 unguarded-merge; verify branch identity before assuming redundant). 1822 and 1864 appear genuinely unique — port them.\n\nUNIQUE to background-refresh.spec.ts (keep): \"uses default author when PM_AUTHOR unset\" 318, \"skips while fresh gate held by another writer\" 229, \"re-dispatches child on sibling enqueue in final window\" 369, \"does not re-dispatch after failure\" 403, dispatchRefreshChild spawn tests 244/264.\n\nSafe merge: port the 2-3 unique search-cache cases above into background-refresh.spec.ts, then delete the shouldRunSearchRefreshInForeground/queue/runSemanticRefreshWorker describe blocks (search-cache ~1712-1946). Re-run coverage; background-refresh.ts must stay 100%."
  "2026-06-16T07:09:41.606Z",claude-code-agent,"[D2 MEDIUM] check-secrets duplicate — exact safe-merge map. Both exercise scripts/check-secrets-lib.mjs scanContent.\n\ncheck-secrets-rules.spec.ts imports the module ONCE at top level (shared RULES, push/pop in try/finally). check-secrets-lib.spec.ts uses createScriptHarness().importModule for a FRESH cache-busted module per test (cleaner isolation — preferred base).\n\nDUPLICATED assertions:\n- one-based line numbers: rules \"reports one-based line numbers\" (line 54, asserts line===3) vs lib \"computes one-based line numbers across multiple newlines\" (16, line===5) AND \"line number of 1 for first line\" (24). Same code path; lib covers more positions.\n- includeFiles scoping: rules \"honors includeFiles when custom rules are scoped\" (39) vs lib \"skips a rule whose includeFiles pattern does not match\" (31). Same branch.\n- excludeFiles scoping: rules \"honors excludeFiles for path/host heuristics\" (34) vs lib \"skips a rule whose excludeFiles pattern matches\" (43). Same branch (absolute-home-path under tests/).\n\nUNIQUE to check-secrets-rules.spec.ts (MUST keep — these are the only places hit):\n- \"flags every GitHub token prefix\" (11): ghp_/gho_/ghu_/ghs_/ghr_ + github_pat_ — github-token rule variants.\n- \"flags other high-risk credential shapes\" (19): private-key, aws-access-key, sentry-org-token, private-ssh-target, private-ip.\n- \"does not flag clean documentation content\" (30): zero-findings path.\n- \"exposes a non-empty rule set\" (60): RULES array shape.\n\nSafe merge: fold the include/exclude + line-number cases into check-secrets-lib.spec.ts (better per-test fresh-module isolation), keep the rule-coverage cases (GitHub prefixes, credential shapes, clean-doc, rule-set shape) — they are NOT in the lib spec and likely cover distinct regex branches. Re-run coverage on check-secrets-lib.mjs."
  "2026-06-16T07:09:41.909Z",claude-code-agent,"[Best-practice cluster] Fake-timers candidates (no coverage change, removes CI flake + speeds suite): replace real setTimeout/sleep with vi.useFakeTimers()/vi.advanceTimersByTimeAsync in: extension-loader.spec.ts ~5030/5043/5067 (deactivate-timeout, 25-35ms real waits + manual process.on(unhandledRejection)); telemetry-runtime.spec.ts ~51/1224/1678; item-store.spec.ts ~469/489 (fs cache poll); embedding-batches.spec.ts ~243. These are the only places real wall-clock waits appear in tests/unit — everything else is mocked. Verify each is a deterministic timeout-branch test before swapping (a couple poll real fs mtime and may need a different approach)."
  "2026-06-16T07:18:00.217Z",claude-code-agent,"Dedup D1+D2 done (suite green: 215 files / 4218 tests, 0 failures via run-tests.mjs test). D1 (search): background-refresh.spec.ts now OWNS all background-refresh tests. Ported 3 genuinely-unique cases from search-cache.spec.ts: 'keeps awaited queue-gate backoff timers referenced' (setTimeout unref assertion), 'processes ids enqueued mid-refresh in a follow-up round' (rounds===2 loop-back), 'returns immediately when the queue is empty' (rounds===0 empty-drain). Deleted the duplicated 'search background refresh' module blocks from search-cache.spec.ts (~235 lines: lock-id, shouldRunSearchRefreshInForeground, pending queue, runSemanticRefreshWorker) and pruned now-unused imports (REINDEX_LOCK_ID/runSemanticRefreshWorker/shouldRunSearchRefreshInForeground/acquireLock); kept drainPendingRefreshIds/enqueuePendingRefreshIds (still used by entrypoint tests) and the cache/entrypoint/isSemanticRefreshActive/searchCacheTestOnly tests that remained inside that describe. Did NOT port search-cache's unguarded-merge test (line 84 already covered by bg spec's mkdirSync-throw test). D2 (check-secrets): kept check-secrets-lib.spec.ts as the single file (createScriptHarness fresh-module isolation). Ported 4 unique tests adapted to harness.importModule: github-token prefix coverage, high-risk credential shapes (private-key/aws/sentry/ssh-target/private-ip, runtime-assembled fixtures incl split 192.168.x.x to avoid self-scan), clean-doc zero-findings, non-empty rule set. Deleted check-secrets-rules.spec.ts entirely (64 lines; its one-based-line/include/exclude tests already exist in lib spec). Coverage of check-secrets-lib.mjs + background-refresh.ts preserved by surviving tests."
close_reason: "Dedup applied: D1 background-refresh + D2 check-secrets merged; 18 redundant tests removed; coverage re-verified 100/100/100/100."
